ked in the queue, watching or waiting, while the white counter and bright, cloudy background keep the scene stark and surreal.\n\nThe view opens back out to the long line. It snakes far into the distance across the cloudy white floor. At the front are several distinctive figures: the Black man in a formal black suit, a person in a glossy black helmet and white outfit with a yellow belt, an older man in a dark robe, and a woman in a dark top and pale skirt. Farther back are people in colorful costumes and everyday clothing, all standing shoulder to shoulder in the same slow queue.\n\nBack at the counter, the man in white looks down at the book, then up toward the elderly man in blue. The elderly man turns his head away, as if reacting to something happening behind him. The scene cuts to the line behind him: a man in a yellow shirt and striped tie stands with his arms raised in complaint. Around him are other waiting figures, including a man in a green cap with plush brown antlers, a man in a yellow cap and green sweater holding golf clubs, and a person in a white fencing outfit with a mesh face mask. The man in yellow suddenly drops straight down through the cloudy floor; only his trouser legs and shoes are briefly visible sinking into a soft, dark-edged hole in the mist.\n\nThe surrounding people react by looking down toward where he vanished. The man in the green cap with antlers bends his head, and the golfer in the yellow cap peers toward the gap while still holding his clubs. The fencer stands stiffly beside them. At the counter, the elderly man in blue turns back toward the man in white with wide eyes, looking startled by what just happened.\n\nA close view shows the man in the green cap with plush antlers now holding and eating a chocolate bar. He wears a purple sleeveless shirt and plaid shorts, and he bites into the partly unwrapped bar while standing in line. Beside him, a woman in a light purple dress with a white cap or bonnet looks downward. The candy wrapper is dark with the familiar Snickers branding colors visible, and the chocolate bar protrudes from the opened end as he eats.\n\nThe commercial then presents the product against a plain white background. A wrapped Snickers bar appears centered, with the blue “SNICKERS” logo on a brown wrapper. Beneath it, bold black text reads, “Really hungry? Why wait?” A much larger Snickers wrapper slides in across the top and fills most of the screen, showing “THE BIG ONE” in large yellow-orange lettering on the left and the oversized blue “SNICKERS” logo across the bar.\n\nFinally, the scene returns to the white counter. The man in white stands behind the podium with the green banker’s lamp and the “Do I Look Like I Care” mug still on top. Two people now wait before him: a Black man in a black suit and tie, and an elderly white woman in a teal dress with a white apron. They stand side by side in the glowing white space, facing the man in white as the next people in line.",
